(RE_V5_CC_AC_NATIVE)
(LinuxCNC RS274/NGC native syntax: G0/G3/G4/G17/G21/G40/G43/G49/G53/G54/G64/G80/G90/G91.1/G94/F/H/I/J/M64/M65/M30)
(Program is fed to the microkernel exactly as opened; no UI G-code rewrite)
(Program model: XYZAC five-turn cylindrical spring, radius 10mm, Z 0 to -50mm)
(A axis swings 45 +/- 10 deg during cutting; C axis rotates with the spring)

G21 G17 G90 G91.1 G40 G49 G80 G94 G54
G64 P0.500 Q0.050

(Restart-safe visible return to program beginning in machine coordinates)
G53 G0 Z0.000
(RTCP/switchkins is controlled by this G-code program only across the spring segment)
G43 H1
G4 P0.050
(Rapid rotary normalization before cutting)
G53 G0 A0.000 C0.000
G53 G0 X0.000 Y0.000

(Rapid non-cut positioning; first feed segment starts from this spring anchor)
G0 X0.000 Y10.000 Z0.000 A45.000 C0.000

(Spring start: enable RTCP before the first spring feed)
M64 P0
G4 P0.050

(Cutting trajectory: one uninterrupted RTCP segment of 20 tangent G3 helical quadrants)
(XYZ uses true radius-10 arc interpolation; no G1 polyline approximation)
(A swings 45->55->45->35->45 each turn while C and Z advance continuously)
